# Multi-Body Orbital Rotation Model (3D)

This simulation visualizes the 3D orbital motion of Earth around the Sun and the Moon around the Earth, incorporating:

- Axial and orbital inclination
- Celestial motion in space
- Time-evolved animation using `matplotlib`

## Celestial Bodies Modeled

- **Sun**: Fixed at origin
- **Earth**: Circular orbit around Sun (1 AU radius)
- **Moon**: Orbits Earth ~13 times per year with ~5° inclination

## Technologies Used

- `matplotlib.pyplot`
- `mplot3d` from `mpl_toolkits`
- `FuncAnimation` for real-time orbital animation

